File: South African musician Lira. AFP JOHANNESBURG - Lira says she is making progress despite still having difficulties with her speech. The 43-year-old afro-pop singer was hospitalised after suffering a stroke in Germany last month. READ: SA singer Lira hospitalised after suffering a stroke The stroke affected her ability to communicate. In her social media accounts, Lira, whose real name is Lerato Molapo, asked fans to continue to pray for her recovery. 